%2F117505210.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Indian%20Man%20Gets%2030-Month%20Jail%20In%20US%20For%20Customs%20Duty%20Evasion%20On%20Jewellery%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EAn%20Indian%20man%20who%20ran%20jewellery%20companies%20in%20New%20York%20has%20been%20sentenced%20to%2030%20months%20in%20prison%20for%20evading%20customs%20duty%20for%20importing%20jewellery%20worth%20more%20than%20USD%2013.5%20million%20and%20for%20illegally%20processing%20over%20USD%2010.3%20million%20through%20an%20unlicensed%20money%20transmitting%20business%2C%20a%20US%20attorney%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EActing%20US%20Attorney%20Vikas%20Khanna%20said%20Monishkumar%20Kirankumar%20Doshi%20Shah%20(4O)%20of%20Mumbai%20and%20Jersey%20City%2C%20New%20Jersey%2C%20previously%20pleaded%20guilty%20before%20US%20District%20Judge%20Esther%20Salas%20to%20a%20two-count%20information%2C%20charging%20him%20with%20conspiracy%20to%20commit%20wire%20fraud%20and%20operating%20and%20aiding%20and%20abetting%20the%20operation%20of%20an%20unlicensed%20money%20transmitting%20business.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%20to%20the%20prison%20term%2C%20the%20judge%20ordered%20restitution%20in%20the%20amount%20of%20USD%20742%2C500%20for%20the%20wire%20fraud%20scheme%20and%20forfeiture%20of%20USD%2011%2C126%2C982.33%20for%20the%20wire%20fraud%20and%20unlicensed%20money%20transmitting%20schemes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAdditionally%2C%20the%20court%20imposed%20a%20two-year%20term%20of%20supervised%20release.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20court%20documents%2C%20from%20around%20December%202019%20to%20around%20April%202022%2C%20Shah%20engaged%20in%20a%20scheme%20to%20evade%20duties%20for%20shipments%20of%20jewellery%20from%20Turkey%20and%20India%20to%20the%20United%20States.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20would%20ship%20and%2For%20instruct%20his%20co-conspirators%20to%20ship%20goods%20from%20Turkey%20or%20India%20%E2%80%94%20which%20would%20have%20been%20subject%20to%20an%20approximately%205.5%20per%20cent%20duty%20if%20shipped%20directly%20to%20the%20United%20States%20%E2%80%94%20to%20one%20of%20his%20companies%20in%20South%20Korea.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShah's%20co-conspirators%20in%20South%20Korea%20would%20change%20the%20labels%20on%20the%20jewellery%20to%20state%20that%20they%20were%20from%20South%20Korea%20instead%20of%20Turkey%20or%20India%2C%20and%20then%20ship%20them%20to%20Shah%20or%20his%20customers%20in%20the%20United%20States%2C%20thereby%20unlawfully%20evading%20the%20duty%2C%20federal%20prosecutors%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShah%20would%20also%20instruct%20his%20customers%20to%20make%20fake%20invoices%20and%20packing%20lists%20to%20make%20it%20look%20like%20his%20South%20Korean%20companies%20were%20actually%20ordering%20jewellery%20from%20Turkey%20or%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20instructed%20a%20third-party%20shipping%20company%20to%20provide%20false%20information%20to%20US%20Customs%20and%20Border%20Protection%20about%20the%20origin%20of%20the%20jewellery.%20During%20the%20stated%20period%2C%20Shah%20shipped%20approximately%20USD%2013.5%20million%20of%20jewellery%20from%20South%20Korea%20to%20the%20United%20States%20without%20paying%20the%20appropriate%20duty.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlso%20from%20July%202020%20to%20November%202021%2C%20Shah%20owned%20and%2For%20operated%20numerous%20jewellery%20companies%20in%20New%20York%20City's%20Diamond%20District%2C%20and%20used%20these%20firms%20to%20conduct%20more%20than%20USD%2010.3%20million%20illegal%20financial%20transactions%20for%20customers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BShah%20would%20also%20collect%20cash%20from%20customers%20and%20use%20other%20individuals'%20jewellery%20companies%20to%20convert%20the%20cash%20into%20wires%20or%20checks.%20At%20times%2C%20Shah%20and%20other%20members%20of%20the%20money-transmitting%20business%20moved%20hundreds%20of%20thousands%20of%20dollars%20in%20a%20single%20day.%20In%20exchange%20for%20their%20services%2C%20certain%20members%20of%20the%20money%20transmitting%20business%